          virtually all graphic designers worked on print media such as posters,
          magazines, billboards, and books. Print designers are typically
          masters of typography, illustration, and traditional printing
          processes like the <span class="highlight">Linotype machine</span> or the
          <span class="highlight">letterpress machine</span>, a 500-year-old
          printing method that has regained popularity in recent years for its
          handmade and traditional feel.
